00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.919
Indices may track stocks within a specific stock exchange or country.

00:00:04.919 --> 00:00:08.550
For example the CSI 300 includes

00:00:08.550 --> 00:00:13.144
stocks that are listed on the Shanghai and Shenzhen Stock Exchanges in China.

00:00:13.144 --> 00:00:19.259
Stocks can also be related by sector for example the Nasdaq 100 technology

00:00:19.260 --> 00:00:22.080
index or Nasdaq financial 100

00:00:22.079 --> 00:00:26.769
index track the performance of stocks in their respective sectors.

00:00:26.769 --> 00:00:30.109
Indices are important to investors because at

00:00:30.109 --> 00:00:33.975
a glance we can quickly check the status of various markets.

00:00:33.975 --> 00:00:37.310
In a way it's checking the pulse of a region or

00:00:37.310 --> 00:00:40.755
sector to evaluate the health of that market.

00:00:40.755 --> 00:00:45.245
Professional investment managers also use indices as benchmarks

00:00:45.244 --> 00:00:50.070
that they either tried to match or outperform with their own portfolios.

